<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="a16Jan1935"><font color="red">16 January 1935</font> <i>NLPL</i> (to Paul L&eacute;on): Fjaell is the word I wanted to know of. In Modern Norwegian no &lsquo;d&rsquo; is in their words after &lsquo;l&rsquo; or &lsquo;n&rsquo; / Grinn for Grind = a gate, / Fjaell for Fjaeld / Mann for Mand = a man / Get me a god beginning with (gamma). Please send <i>Irish Times</i> regularly as I pass it on to Lucia and in this way she reads a good deal &hellip; I can&apos;t write letters &hellip; I got the books &hellip; I think porkbarrel bore connection originally with some river transport &hellip; My brother in Triest has been writing constantly for money &hellip; What the childless, teetotaller, non smoker does with his money I don&apos;t know. </div>
